full_text: In this demonstration, we create a new underwriting rule for buildings built before 1950, for a business owner's submission. It should be evaluated before quote time, and it blocks bind. First log in a super user. Go to Administration. Select Business Settings, Business Rules, Underwriting Rules. Click Add. Enter the required fields to define the rule on the Rule Details tab. You can configure the Advanced tab in the demonstration for approving underwriting issue later. Click the Code field. The code must be unique. Select Prequote as the checking set since it should be evaluated before quote time, and it will be a new underwriting. Select Blocked. Select Blocked. Select Blocked. Bind for Blocking Point. In the Applies to section, click Selected for Policy Lines. Two boxes and arrow buttons appear. Select Bob. Click the Right arrow to add it to the selected list on the right. Click the Context drop-down field. Select the Rule Details tab. Select the Rule Context business owner's policy for each building, which provides data and objects to the buildings on the policy. Click in the Expression field. The list of available objects are displayed for the selected Rule Context. Select the Object Bop Building. Type a dot to show the fields on the object. Select Building. Type a dot. Select Year Build. Select Year Build. Click the Operation drop-down field. In the Operation drop-down, select the Less Than sign. Click the Right Expression field. In the Right Expression field, type in the number 1950. Click anywhere outside to refresh the page. The error went away after the page is refreshed. Next, set Underwriting Issue Details. Use the syntax of $ and curly braces to wrap the policy objects. The fixed ID of an object is unique, so it can be used as the Issue Key to identify the Underwriter Issue once it is raised. The Value field is not visible, because Value Comparator on the Advanced tab is set as None. Enter the Short Description for the Underwriting Issue for all languages. Click the English Text field. Enter the Long Description for the Underwriting Issue for all languages. Enter the Long Description for the Underwriting Issue for all languages. Save the rule. Click the Gear icon. Log out. Log in as Producer Archie Armstrong. Create a Business Owner's Submission. Building 1 has the Year Built Set as 1940. Click on the row for Building 2. Building 2 has the Year Built Set as 1920. Click Quote. Go to Risk Analysis. The Underwriting Issue, Building Built before 1950 is created and it is blocking bind. The Year is not displayed with the issue, because we did not configure the Underwriting Rule to record the associated value. The Approve button is grayed out for the issue, because the agent does not have the authority. This is the end of the demonstration for creating a new Underwriting Rules with fields that define the issue.
